ğŸŒ STEP 1 â€” Generate SSH Key (Local Machine)
ssh-keygen -t rsa -b 4096 -f ~/.ssh/new-akhil-key


Files created:

~/.ssh/new-akhil-key
~/.ssh/new-akhil-key.pub

âš™ï¸ STEP 2 â€” Terraform Infrastructure Setup

Go to terraform folder:

cd terraform


Initialize:

terraform init


Validate:

terraform validate


Deploy:

terraform apply -auto-approve


Terraform will create:

âœ” EC2 instance (t3.micro free-tier)
âœ” Security Group (Ports 22, 80)
âœ” Upload AWS KeyPair using your public key

ğŸ–¥ï¸ STEP 3 â€” SSH into EC2
ssh -i ~/.ssh/new-akhil-key ec2-user@<EC2_PUBLIC_IP>

ğŸ³ STEP 4 â€” Install Docker on EC2
sudo yum update -y
sudo yum install docker -y
sudo systemctl start docker
sudo systemctl enable docker
sudo usermod -aG docker ec2-user
exit


Reconnect:

ssh -i ~/.ssh/new-akhil-key ec2-user@<EC2_PUBLIC_IP>

ğŸ“¥ STEP 5 â€” Clone Repo & Build Docker on EC2
git clone https://github.com/<your-user>/event-management-devops.git
cd event-management-devops
docker build -t event-app .


Run container:

docker run -d -p 80:80 event-app


Verify:

docker ps


Access app:

http://<EC2_PUBLIC_IP>

âš¡ STEP 6 â€” CREATE CI/CD PIPELINE (GitHub Actions)

Create folder:

mkdir -p .github/workflows


Create pipeline file:

nano .github/workflows/deploy.yml


Paste the FULL PIPELINE below:

â­â­â­ GITHUB ACTIONS CI/CD PIPELINE (deploy.yml) â­â­â­
name: Deploy to EC2 using Docker

on:
  push:
    branches:
      - main

jobs:
  deploy:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest

    steps:
    # Step 1: Checkout Code
    - name: Checkout repository
      uses: actions/checkout@v3

    # Step 2: Install SSH Key
    - name: Setup SSH Key
      uses: webfactory/ssh-agent@v0.7.0
      with:
        ssh-private-key: ${{ secrets.EC2_SSH_KEY }}

    # Step 3: Copy project files to EC2
    - name: Copy project to EC2
      run: |
        rsync -avz -e "ssh -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no" ./ ec2-user@${{ secrets.EC2_PUBLIC_IP }}:/home/ec2-user/event-management-devops/

    # Step 4: Restart Docker Container on EC2
    - name: Deploy Docker on EC2
      run: |
        ssh -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no ec2-user@${{ secrets.EC2_PUBLIC_IP }} << 'EOF'
        cd event-management-devops
        docker rm -f event-app || true
        docker build -t event-app .
        docker run -d -p 80:80 --name event-app event-app
        EOF

ğŸ” STEP 7 â€” Add GitHub Secrets

Go to:

GitHub â†’ Repo â†’ Settings â†’ Secrets â†’ Actions â†’ New Repository Secret


Add:

Secret Name	Value
EC2_PUBLIC_IP	Your EC2 Public IP
EC2_SSH_KEY	content of ~/.ssh/new-akhil-key (private key)

To copy private key:

cat ~/.ssh/new-akhil-key


Paste into GitHub (do NOT share it).

ğŸš€ STEP 8 â€” How CI/CD Works Now

Whenever you push code to main:

GitHub Actions connects to EC2

Sends updated code

Rebuilds Docker image

Restarts container

Deploys new version

No manual SSH needed.

ğŸ§ª STEP 9 â€” Test CI/CD

Make ANY change:

git add .
git commit -m "CI/CD test update"
git push origin main


Go to:

GitHub â†’ Actions â†’ workflow running

Deployment will auto-update the live app.

